'''''X-Wing: Solo Command''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] novel written by [[Aaron Allston]]. It is the seventh volume of the [[Star Wars: X-Wing (novel series)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'' novel series]], and it was first published by [[Bantam Spectra]] on [[February 2]], [[1999]]. A sequel, ''[[X-Wing: Isard's Revenge]]'', was published later that year.

==Publisher's summary==
''Wraith Squadron: they are the Rebel Alliance's ultimate strike force. Sleek, swift, and deadly, they are the first in battle, the last line of defense. Now they must find and destroy a wily enemy more powerful than the Empire itself.''

''Their covert mission has been a success. The enemy has been vanquished. Or so they thought. The Super Star Destroyer ''Iron Fist'' somehow escaped destruction and with it the New Republic's greatest threat, the infamous warlord Zsinj. To defeat him, Wraith Squadron must join a combat task force led by the only man crafty enough to beat Zsinj at his own game: Han Solo. But Zsinj knows the X-wing fighters' indomitable courage is both their greatest strength&mdash;and their greatest weakness. For even against the most overwhelming odds, the Rebels will fight to the death. And that will leave Zsinj the galaxy's unchallenged master!''

==Plot summary==
[[Wraith Squadron|Wraith Squadron]] is formally incorporated into the [[New Republic Defense Fleet/Legends|fleet]] commanded by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] to hunt down [[Warlord/Legends|Warlord]] [[Zsinj]], a task force that includes [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] and the [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] [[MC80B Star Cruiser|cruiser]] ''[[Mon Remonda]]''. After narrowly surviving an attack by Zsinj's forces at [[Levian II]], the Wraiths attempt to lure Zsinj into a trap using a fake [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] (the ''[[Millennium Falsehood]]'' as bait. The Wraiths target the ''[[Binring Biomedical Product]]'' facilities on [[Saffalore]], the [[Laboratory/Legends|laboratory]] that altered [[Voort saBinring|Piggy]]. The same medical research, now under the supervision of [[Doctor/Legends|Dr.]] [[Edda Gast]] aboard Zsinj's [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]] [[Iron Fist (Executor-class)|''Iron Fist'']], is creating [[Sleeper agent/Legends|sleeper agents]] among [[Alien/Legends|aliens]] in the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. The Saffalore outpost is a trap, and the Wraiths barely escape with Rogue Squadron's assistance.

The sleeper agent program, dubbed [[Project Minefield]], targets influential New Republic [[Officer/Legends|officials]] for [[Death/Legends|assassination]] and is meant to sow dissent between [[Human/Legends|human]] and alien allies in the fledging government. Dr. Gast is captured by the New Republic, and she offers intelligence on Project Minefield in exchange for sanctuary. [[Myn Donos]] and [[Lara Notsil]] begin a relationship, but the Wraiths become overly curious about her shrouded past. [[Garik Loran|Face]] discovers her to be [[Gara Petothel]], an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] double [[Agent/Legends|agent]], and Myn is particularly hurt by this revelation as Gara, when working for [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit|Trigit]], was an accessory to the destruction of his original unit. Gara flees her squadmates and rejoins Zsinj's forces. Determined to clear her name and her conscience, she plots to sabotage's Zsinj's plans and the ''Iron Fist'' from within.

The honor-minded Admiral [[Teren Rogriss]] of the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] [[Agonizer (starship)|Agonizer]] secretly contacts Han Solo to assist him in the battle against Warlord Zsinj. Rogriss supplies Solo with an [[Immobilizer 418 Interdictor-class Heavy Cruiser|interdictor cruiser]] that Solo uses to ambush Zsinj in the [[Vahaba system/Legends|Vahaba system]]. The slippery Zsinj escapes this trap, fleeing to the [[Selaggis system/Legends|Selaggis system]] where another confrontation takes place. The ''Iron Fist's'' [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] is ruined by Gara, momentarily stranding the ship in the Selaggis system. As she escapes the Imperial warship, Gara frees as many of the Project Minefield patients as she can. She alerts the New Republic to the ''Iron Fist's'' position, drawing Solo's task force in for the kill. 

But in another act of deception, Zsinj escapes, using [[Orbital nightcloak|nightcloak]] technology and the carefully laid debris of the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|Super Star Destroyer]] ''[[Razor's Kiss]]'' to disguise his massive ship departure. The hunt for the warlord will continue, though Wraith Squadron is dissolved as a fighter unit, its agents absorbed into [[New Republic Intelligence Service|New Republic Intelligence]].

==Legacy==
In [[2014]], [[Paul Youll]]'s ''X-Wing: Solo Command'' cover art was used in the ''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Miniatures Game]]'', appearing on the card "Decoy."<ref name="FFGXW">{{FFGXW|set=Z-95 Headhunter Expansion Pack|cardname=Decoy}}</ref>

